cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference Cortex-OS in academic or professional work, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Cortex-OS: A Cascading Constitutional Architecture for AI Operating Systems on Claude Code"
abstract: >
  Cortex-OS is a public reference implementation of a layered control system
  for AI agent operation built on Claude Code's native primitives. Four
  layers compose the pattern: cascading CLAUDE.md constitutions, deterministic
  bash hooks, hub-and-spoke agent teams with enforced context boundaries, and
  schema-driven configuration. The repository ships a reference business
  example, a runtime utility layer for inspection and validation, and the
  documentation that makes the pattern forkable.
